The statistics for 30 June, made public on the Mpumalanga Department of Health’s Facebook page just before 12:00 today (2 July), reveals that one person has passed away due to Covid-19. It is unclear who the person is and what the circumstances around the death is. The Covid-19 statistics released by the Department of Health on 30 June. Statistics also show that positive cases in the STLM area have increased with 19 from 30 June to 1 July. • Some local residents were convinced that a person buried over the weekend was Middelburg’s first Covid-19 fatality.